      "scientific": "Syzygium cumini",
      "common": "Java Plum",
      "khmer": "ព្រេីង",
      "genus": "Syzygium",
      "nickname": "Jamie",
      "image": "image/catalogue/2.jpg",
      "map": "map.html#tree-2",
      "mapX": 9.5,
      "mapY": 69.5,
      "description": "A favorite cultural snack eaten seasonally at the end of the dry season, the Java Plum is a fruit found on trees all across Cambodia. During the period of Khmer New Year, it is commonly eaten as a snack with dipping salts composed of salt, sugar, MSG, and chili peppers. Fun fact: compounds in the fruit can stain your tongue purple and blue.",
      "cite": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syzygium_cumini",
