      "mapX": 47,
      "mapY": 62.7,
      "description": "Renowned as the national flower of Cambodia, the rumduol flower is a flower that can be found almost everywhere in the country. Predominantly found around the ancient temples of Siem Reap Province, this flower gives off a sweet scent around its blooming months (December to April). It has been featured in carvings on temple walls for centuries and serves as a vital part of Cambodian history. Fun fact: Despite being mainly known for its flowers, the rumduol tree actually has fruit too!",
